(42, 1, 3, 46, 7, 40, 40, 'having had perfect understanding', 'Judgment and Understanding Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of discernment and understanding in both passages. Luke emphasizes a ''perfect understanding'' while Paul expresses his judgment, suggesting a shared value in wisdom and insight.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 1, 3, 46, 16, 12, 12, 'to write unto thee in order', 'Desire for Order and Timing', 'This connection highlights the theme of careful planning and timing in both passages. Luke expresses a desire to write in order, while Paul discusses Apollos''s timing for visiting, emphasizing the importance of appropriate moments for action.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 1, 3, 19, 40, 5, 5, 'in order', 'Connection of Order and Works', 'This connection highlights the theme of order in relation to God''s works. Luke''s mention of writing ''in order'' parallels the psalmist''s acknowledgment that God''s ''wonderful works'' cannot be ''reckoned up in order.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
